    <section class="blogs-details-area">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-md-8">
            <div class="row">
              <div class="blogs-inner-div">
                <%= image_tag("blogfeed/blog-detail.png", alt:"blog-detail" )%>
                <p>
                  In today's fast-paced, digital world, small business owners
                  have more lending options than ever before. While traditional
                  bank loans are still popular, there are many other avenues
                  that potential borrowers can now explore. Here are four types
                  of business financing options.
                </p>

                <p class="p-common">1. Bank Loans and Alternative Lenders</p>

                <p>
                  Alternative lenders offering cash advances without the need
                  for collateral are a popular way for small business owners to
                  secure funding. The downside of bank loans is that they can be
                  difficult to secure, especially for those with poor credit.
                  Alternative lenders like Seamless Capital offer instant
                  qualification, even for those with less than stellar credit.
                </p>

                <p class="p-common">2. Credit Card Financing</p>

                <p>
                  Credit cards are a necessity for most small business owners.
                  These handy little pieces of plastic make it possible to
                  finance things that might otherwise be out of reach such as
                  new equipment or advertising. However, credit card debt,
                  especially large credit card cash advances, are also risky.
                  High interest rates and fees, combined with small minimum
                  monthly payments, leave you working off the balance over
                  decades rather than years.
                </p>

                <p class="p-common">3. Purchase Order Financing</p>

                <p>
                  Purchase order financing is funding for businesses that don't
                  yet have the cash flow to fulfill customer requests. Purchase
                  order financing is a great option for companies that have
                  product demand, but lack immediate access to the money they
                  need to pay suppliers.
                </p>

                <p class="p-common">4. Merchant Cash Advance</p>

                <p>
                  Merchant cash advances provide business owners with a lump sum
                  of money upfront. For example, our Seamless cash advance
                  provides you with financing that is secured by anticipated
                  credit card and/or debit card sales.
                </p>

                <p>
                  Are you a small business owner looking to fund a growth plan
                  or your next big project? Seamless Capital Access can help. We
                  offer quick cash using a simple qualification process. One
                  application, multiple lenders, fewer fees. Apply now.
                </p>
              </div>
